
[1]alexipharmic

   ALEXIPH'ARMIC, a. [Gr. to expel, and poison.]

   Expelling poison; antidotal; sudorific; that has the quality of
   expelling poison or infection by sweat.

   ALEXIPH'ARMIC, n. A medicine that is intended to obviate the effects of
   poison; an antidote to poison or infection. By the Greeks, the word was
                             used for an amulet.
